Elasticity of demand means that when the demand changes, the price changes.  When the demand of a product goes up, the company can make the price of their product/service go up as well.  If the demand goes down, the price of the product may have to decrease in order to make money.  The demand of goods is what determines the price.


Question 9: Bayes' therom is that the more possibilities there are, the more possible outcomes there are.  For example, when testing an employee for drugs, you can test them and if the test comes up positive then you know they were using drugs.  If an employee's test comes up negative, it doesn't mean that they haven't been using drugs.  It could mean that they weren't using them at all, or that the drugs had left their system in time for their testing.
